obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24708)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24708&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[On and from the appointed day, in relation to the National`
  line `Institute of Pharmaceutical Education and Research, Mohali],--`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Society in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference to ^2[that Institute];`
  line
  line `^3[(aa) all property, movable and immovable of, or belonging to, the Society, shall vest in that Institute;]`
  line
  line `(b) all the rights and liabilities of the Society shall be transferred to, and be the rights and`
  line `liabilities of, ^2[that Institute]; and`
  line
  line `(c) every person employed by the Society immediately before the appointed day shall hold office or service in ^2[that Institute] by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension, leave, gratuity, provident fund and other matters as he would have held the same if this Act had not been passed, and shall continue to be so unless and until his employment is terminated or until such tenure, remuneration and terms`
  line `and condition are duly altered by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may be terminated by ^2[that Institute] in accordance with the terms of the contract with the employee or, if no provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by ^2[that Institute] of compensation`
  line `equivalent to three months remuneration in the case of permanent employee and one month's remuneration in the case of other employee`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021 s. 9, for dbtqsOn and from the appointed daydbtqs (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24709)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24709&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Functions of ^1[Institutes].--`
  line `The functions of the Institute shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) to nurture and promote quality and excellence in pharmaceutical education and research;`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) to develop courses leading to graduate and post graduate degrees, doctoral and post-doctoral distinctions and research in pharmaceutical education or to develop integrated courses relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(iia) to conduct executive education courses, short-term certificate courses, training programmes, online or distant education, diploma courses and such other short-term executive courses;]`
  line
  line `(iii) to hold examinations and grant degrees;`
  line
  line `(iv) to confer honorary awards or other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(v) to cooperate with educational or other institutions having objects wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute ^3[by promoting collaborative research, exchange of faculty members, researchers] and scholars and generally in such manner as may be conducive to their common`
  line objective;
  line
  line `(vi) to conduct courses for teachers, pharmaceutical technologists, community and hospital pharmacists and other professionals;`
  line
  line `(vii) to collect and maintain world literature on pharmaceutical and related sciences and`
  line `technology so as to develop an information centre of its own kind for other institutions within the`
  line `country and in the developing world;`
  line
  line `(viii) to create a central faculty of pharmaceutical instrumentation and analysis for use by the`
  line `researchers within and outside the Institute;`
  line
  line `(ix) to have a centre to experiment and innovate and to train teachers and other workers in the art`
  line `or science of pharmaceutical teaching;`
  line
  line `(x) to develop a world level centre for creation of new knowledge and transmission of existing`
  line `information in pharmaceutical areas, with focus on national, educational, professional and industrial`
  line commitments;
  line
  line `^4[(xa) to establish Centres of Excellence for drug discovery and development and medical devices;]`
  line
  line `(xi) to develop a multi-disciplinary approach in carrying out research and training of`
  line `pharmaceutical manpower so that the larger interests of the profession, academia and pharmaceutical`
  line `industry are better served and a pharmaceutical work culture is evolved which is in tune with the`
  line `changing world trends and patterns of pharmaceutical education and research;`
  line
  line `(xii) to organise national or international symposia, seminars and conferences in selected areas of`
  line `pharmaceutical education, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(xiii) to arrange courses catering to the special needs of the developing countries;`
  line
  line `(xiv) to act as a nucleus for interaction between academic and industry by encouraging exchange`
  line `of scientist and other technical staff between the Institute and the industry and by undertaking`
  line `sponsored and funded research as well as consultancy projects by the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(xv) to pay due attention to studies on the distribution and usage of drugs by the rural masses,`
  line `taking into account the socio-economic spectrum in the country.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 10, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "by exchange of faculty members" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 10, ibid (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24710)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Powers of Board of an Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 11, for “Board” (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24710&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Powers of ^1[Board of an Institute].--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the ^1[Board of an Institute] shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the Institute and shall exercise all the powers not otherwise provided for by this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, and shall have the power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the ^1[Board of an Institute] shall--`
  line
  line `(a) take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) fix, demand and receive fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(c) supervise and control the residence and regulate the discipline of students of the Institute and to make arrangements for promoting their health, general welfare and cultural and corporate life;`
  line
  line `(d) institute academic and other posts and to make appointments thereto (except in the case of the Director);`
  line
  line `(e) frame Statutes and Ordinances and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(f) institute and award fellowship, scholarship, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(g) consider and pass resolutions on the annual report, the annual accounts and the budget estimates of the Institute for the next financial year as it thinks fit together with a statement of its development plans; and`
  line
  line `(h) do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or any of the aforesaid powers.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[Board of an Institute] shall have the power to appoint such committees as it considers`
  line `necessary for the exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 4, the ^1[Board of an Institute]`
  line `shall not dispose of in any manner any immovable property without the prior approval of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24711)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Institutes to be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24711&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[Institutes] to be open to all races, creeds and classes.--(1)^2[Every Institute] shall be open to`
  line `persons of either sex and of whatever race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be imposed`
  line `as to religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, teachers or workers or in`
  line `any other connection whatsoever..`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by ^3[any Institute] which in the`
  line `opinion of the Board involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 12, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "The Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24712)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Teaching at Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24712&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Teaching at ^1[Institutes].--All teaching at ^2`
  line `[each of the Institutes] shall be conducted by or in the name of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and the Ordinances made in this behalf.`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 13, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24713)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24713&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of ^1[every Institute].`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of ^2`
  line `[any Institute] and to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Visitor may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon receipt of any such report, the Visitor may take such action and issue such directions as he`
  line `considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the Institute shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 13, for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24714)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Authorities of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24714&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Authorities of ^1[Institutes].--The following shall be the other authorities of ^2[an Institute], namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Senate;`
  line
  line `(b) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 15, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24715)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021 s. 16, for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24715&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Senate of ^1[each Institute] shall consist of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Director, ex officio, who shall be the Chairperson of the Senate;`
  line
  line `(b) the Dean, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) five professors of the Institute, to be nominated by the Chairperson in consultation with the`
  line `Director, by rotation;`
  line
  line `(d) three persons, not being employees of the Institute, to be nominated by the Chairperson in`
  line `consultation with the Director, from among educationists of repute, one each from the fields of`
  line `science, engineering and humanities and one of them shall be either from the Scheduled Castes or`
  line `from the Scheduled Tribes; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other members of the staff as may be laid down in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24716)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 17, for "senate of the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24716&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the`
  line `^1[senate of each Institute] shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the maintenance of standards of instruction, education and examination in the Institute and shall exercise such`
  line `other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24717)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Functions, powers and duties of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24717&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside at`
  line `the meetings of the Board and at the Convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson to ensure that the decisions taken by the Board are`
  line implemented.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24718)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title Director.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 18, for "Director of the Institute shall be appointed by the Board" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24718&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Director of each Institute shall be appointed by the Council] with the prior`
  line `approval of the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration and academic performance of the Institute and for imparting of`
  line `instruction and maintenance of discipline therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director shall submit annual reports and accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to`
  line `him by this Act or the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24719)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title Dean.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 19, for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24719&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Dean of ^1[each Institute] shall be appointed on such terms and conditions as may`
  line `be laid down by the Statutes and shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be assigned`
  line `to him by this Act or the Statutes or the Director..`
  line
  line `(2) The Dean shall report to the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24720)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 20, for "Registrar of the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24720&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Registrar of each Institute] shall be appointed on such terms and conditions`
  line `as may be laid down by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of records, the common seal, the funds of`
  line `the Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the Board, the Senate and such committees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director for the proper discharge of his functions.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned`
  line `to him by this Act or the Statutes or the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24721)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers and duties of other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24721&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The powers and duties of authorities and`
  line `officers, other than those hereinbefore mentioned, shall be determined by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24722)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24722&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of ^1[enabling the Institutes] to discharge its`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, ^2[pay to each Institute] in each financial year such sums of money and in such manner as it may think fit..`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 21, for "enabling the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "pay to the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24723)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Fund of Institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24723&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Fund of ^1[Institutes].--(1) ^2[Every Institute shall] maintain a Fund to which shall be credited—`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `the Institute may, with the approval of the Central Government, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute including expenses`
  line `incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 22, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "The Institute shall" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24724)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Setting up of endowment fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 23, for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24724&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 21, the Central`
  line `Government may direct ^1[every Institute] to--`
  line
  line `(a) set up an endowment fund and any other fund for specified purpose;`
  line
  line `(b) transfer money from its Fund to endowment fund or any other fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24725)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24725&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Every Institute[ shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance-sheet, in such form as may be specified, in accordance with such general directions as may be issued by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of ^2[every Institute] shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute`
  line `to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `((3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection with the audit of the ^3[accounts of any Institute] shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect the offices of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of ^2[every Institute] as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 24, for "The Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for "accounts of the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24726)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Pension and provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 25, for "The Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24726&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[Every Institute] shall constitute, for the benefit of its`
  line `employees, including the Director, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes, such pension, insurance and provident funds as it may deem fit.`
  line .
  line
  line `(2) Where any such provident fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may declare that`
  line `the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) shall apply to such fund as if it were a`
  line `Government provident fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24727)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title Appointments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 26, for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24727&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of ^1[an Institute], except that of the Director, shall be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statutes--`
  line
  line `(a) by the Board, if the appointment is made on the academic staff in the post of Assistant`
  line `Professor or above or if the appointment is made on the non-academic staff in any cadre, the`
  line `maximum of the pay-scale for which is the same or higher than that of Assistant Professor; and`
  line
  line `(b) by the Director, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24728)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24728&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the formation of departments of teaching;`
  line
  line `(b) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(c) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of officers, teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the reservation of posts for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other categories of`
  line `persons as may be determined by the Central Government, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(e) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) the constitution, powers and duties of the authorities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) the establishment and maintenance of halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of filling vacancies among members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(i) the authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board;`
  line
  line `(j) the meetings of the Senate, the quorum at such meetings and the procedure to be followed in`
  line `the conduct of their business; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which by this Act is to be, or may be, prescribed by the Statutes`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24729)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24729&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of the Institute shall be framed by the Board with the`
  line `previous approval of the Visitor and a copy of the same shall be laid as soon as may be before each House`
  line `of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner hereafter in this section provided.`
  line
  line `(3) A new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require the`
  line `previous approval of the Visitor who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit it to the Board for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (24730)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 28, Act 43 of 2021 for "Ordinances of the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24730&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the ^1[Ordinances of each Institute] may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other categories of person;`
  line
  line `(c) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree courses and to the`
  line `examinations of the Institute and shall be eligible for degrees;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the`
  line `examinations of degrees of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and the levying of the fees for residence`
  line `in the halls and hostels and of other charges; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be, or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (24731)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24731&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be`
  line `made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next succeeding meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinances and such`
  line `Ordinances shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (24732)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24732&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee, and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter which is required by subsection`
  line `(1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (85245)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 32
  title `Establishment of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 29, (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85245&sectionno=30A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[CHAPTER II-A`
  line
  line `^THE COUNCIL`
  line
  line `30A. Establishment of Council.-- (1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, there shall be established for all the Institutes specified in column (3) of the Schedule, a central body to be called the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Minister in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having administrative control of the Pharmaceuticals, ex officio, as Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Minister of State in the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having administrative control of the Pharmaceuticals, ex officio, as Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having administrative control of the Pharmaceuticals, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chairperson of every Board of Governors, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director of every Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Chairperson, All India Council for Technical Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) the Director General, Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) four Secretaries to the Government of India, to represent the Ministries or Departments of the Central Government dealing with Biotechnology, Health Research, Higher Education and Science and Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) not less than three, but not more than five persons to be nominated by the Visitor, at least one of whom shall be a woman, having special knowledge or practical experience in education, pharmaceutical industry, medical devices industry or pharmaceutical research;`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b:
  sectionId (85247)
  sectionNo 30B
  orderNo 33
  title `Term of office of, vacancies among, and allowances payable to, members of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85247&sectionno=30B&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the term of office of a member of the Council shall be three`
  line `years from the date of his nomination or election, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of a member elected under clause (j) of sub-section (2) of section 30A shall come to an end as soon as he becomes a Minister or Minister of State or Deputy Minister, or the Speaker or the Deputy Speaker of the House of the People, or the Deputy Chairperson of the Council of States or ceases to be a member of the House which elected him.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of a member nominated or elected to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for the`
  line `remainder of the term of the member in whose place he has been nominated or elected.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section an outgoing member shall, unless the Central`
  line `Government otherwise directs, continue in office until another person is nominated or elected as a`
  line `member in his place.`
  line
  line `(6) The members of the Council shall be paid such travelling and other allowances by the Central`
  line `Government as may be determined by that Government, but no member shall be entitled to any salary by`
  line `reason of this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_c:
  sectionId (85249)
  sectionNo 30C
  orderNo 34
  title `Functions of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85249&sectionno=30C&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the general duty of the Council to coordinate the`
  line `activities of all the Institutes and to take all such steps as to ensure planned and coordinated development`
  line `of pharmaceutical education and research and maintenance of standards thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Council shall perform the following`
  line `functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to advise on matters relating to the duration of the courses, the degrees and other academic`
  line `distinctions to be conferred by the Institutes, admission standards and other academic matters;`
  line
  line `(b) to lay down policy regarding cadres, methods of recruitment and conditions of service of`
  line `employees, institution of scholarships and free-ships, levying of fees and other matters of common interest;`
  line
  line `(c) to examine the development plans of each Institute and to approve such of them as are`
  line `considered necessary and also to indicate broadly the financial implications of such approved plans;`
  line
  line `(d) to lay down policy or guidelines for promoting research and development in pharmaceuticals`
  line `and related areas, fostering collaboration and overseeing developments and on matters incidental thereto;`
  line
  line `(e) to examine the annual budget estimates of each Institute and to recommend to the Central`
  line `Government the allocation of funds for that purpose;`
  line
  line `(f) to advise the Visitor, if so required, in respect of any function to be performed by him under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(g) to perform such other functions as are assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall meet at least once every six months and follow such procedure in its meetings`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_d:
  sectionId (85251)
  sectionNo 30D
  orderNo 35
  title `Chairman of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85251&sectionno=30D&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_d_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the Council shall ordinarily preside at the`
  line `meetings of the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the absence of the Chairperson, the Vice-Chairperson shall preside at the meetings of the Council:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the absence of both the Chairperson and the Vice-Chairperson, any other`
  line `member, chosen from amongst themselves by the members present at the meeting shall preside at that`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Chairperson of the Council to ensure that the decisions taken by the`
  line `Council are implemented.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as are assigned to`
  line `him by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_e:
  sectionId (85253)
  sectionNo 30E
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules in respect of matters in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85253&sectionno=30E&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_30_e_content:
  string
  line `--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of filling vacancies among the members of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the disqualifications for being chosen as, and for being, a member of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances in which, and the authority by which, members may be removed;`
  line
  line `(d) the meetings of the Council and the procedure of conducting business thereat;`
  line
  line `(e) the travelling and other allowances payable to members of the Council; and`
  line
  line `(f) the functions of the Council and the manner in which such functions may be exercised.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Chapter shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_e_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (24733)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 37
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 30, for "No act of the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24733&sectionno=31&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[No act of the Council or any Institute[ or Board or Senate or any other body set up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in, the constitution thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of person acting as a member thereof, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (24734)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 38
  title `Grant of degrees, etc., by Institutes.`
  content `Grant of degrees, etc., by ^1[Institutes].--Notwithstanding anything contained in the University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) or in any other law for the time being in force, ^2[every Institute] shall have power to grant degrees and other academic distinctions and titles under this Act.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24734&sectionno=32&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 31, for "Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "the Institute" (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (24735)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 39
  title `Sponsored schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24735&sectionno=33&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Institute receives funds from any Government, the`
  line `University Grants Commission or any other agency sponsoring a scheme to be executed by the Institute,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount received shall be kept by the Institute separately from the Fund of the Institute and`
  line `utilised only for the purpose of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) the staff required to execute the same shall be recruited in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions stipulated by the sponsoring organisation:`
  line
  line `Provided that any money remaining unutilised under clause (a) shall be transferred to the endowment`
  line `fund created under section 22 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (85244)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 33, (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=85244&sectionno=33A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Power of Central Government to issue directions.-- The Institute shall carry out such directions as may be issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient`
  line `administration of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (24736)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24736&sectionno=34&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `or give such directions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (24737)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 42
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2021, s. 34, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 25-5-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24737&sectionno=35&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of the Society functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for the`
  line `Institute under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this Act, the members of the`
  line `Board holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) Until the first statutes and the Ordinances in relation to the institutes mentioned in column (3) of the Schedule are made under this Act, the Statues and the Ordinances of the National Institute of Pharmaceutical Education and Research, Sector-67, S.A.S. Nagar (Mohali), District Ropar, Punjab as in force, shall apply to those Institutes with the necessary modifications and adaptations in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (24738)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 43
  title `Statutes and Ordinances to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24738&sectionno=36&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the Statute or Ordinance or both Houses agree that the Statute or Ordinance should not be`
  line `made, the Statute or Ordinance shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect,`
  line `as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to`
  line `the validity of anything previously done under that Statute or Ordinance.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make the Statutes or the Ordinances shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act to the Statutes or the Ordinances`
  line `or any of them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute or Ordinance so as to prejudicially`
  line `affect the interests of any person to whom such Statute or Ordinance may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (24739)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 44
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357&sectionId=24739&sectionno=37&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_72_00001_199813_1517807323357
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Institute of Pharmaceutical Education and Research`
  line `Ordinance, 1998 (Ord. 9 of 1998) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
